The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 March is 234,698 (27,050.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 March, there were 4,712 new confirmed cases (543.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 February, there were 4,041 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 17% (671 extra cases).
